        public ObjectReader nextObjectMetadata()

For example if you call ObjectReader.beginObject() you wont be able to do it anymore (however you still can retrieve the metadata!).

      • consumeLiteral

        protected final ValueType consumeLiteral()
                                  throws IOException
        Reads the next literal value into _booleanValue, _doubleValue or _intValue and returns the type of the readed literal, possible values are : INTEGER, DOUBLE, BOOLEAN, NULL. When calling this method the _cursor must be positioned on the first character of the value in the _buffer, you can ensure that by calling readNextToken(boolean).
        Throws:
        IOException
